      "message": "Hi Tetsui,\n\nThanks for investigating the issue!\n\nRegarding where to put this logic, we\u0027re trying to move as much Chrome OS specific logic from the framework (platform/tast) to test bundles (platform/tast-tests) for better separation between the framework and test bundles, as well as better availability of support libraries (framework code can\u0027t import rich support libraries available in tast-tests).\n\nIn this case I think we can run the logic as pre/post-run hooks. I know that it\u0027s best if we can enable audit before running a bundle, but I hope it\u0027s practically okay since SIGKILL is sent in the middle of bundle execution.\n\nSince pre/post-run hooks are not well supported in Tast yet, I\u0027ve sent a framework change to add support of it: crrev.com/c/2513683. Can you take a look to see if it fits your use case?\n\nThank you!\n",
